<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,438,1121]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
HABITAT RECORDS: Wide variety of habitats. Shallow water, adhering to stones, quiet water area at the edge of a stream and a lake (
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, P. D." box="[357,508,1059,1085]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="3 - 554" refId="ref5273" refString="Perkins, P. D. (1980) Aquatic beetles of the family Hydraenidae in the Western Hemisphere: classification, biogeography and inferred phylogeny (Insecta: Coleoptera). Quaestiones entomologicae, 16, 3 - 554." type="journal article" year="1980">Perkins 1980</bibRefCitation>
); temporary pools, with muddy substrate, pools in sand dunes, and margins of small streams (
<bibRefCitation author="Valladares, L. F. &amp; Short, A. E. Z." box="[251,532,1095,1121]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="63 - 68" refId="ref5932" refString="Valladares, L. F. &amp; Short, A. E. Z. (2011) Revision of the Ochthebiinae of Venezuela (Coleoptera: Hydraenidae). Zootaxa, 3021 (1), 63 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3021.1.4" type="journal article" year="2011">Valladares &amp; Short 2011</bibRefCitation>
); lakes, ponds and rock pools (
<bibRefCitation author="Benetti, C. J. &amp; Valladares, L. F. &amp; Delgado, J. A. &amp; Hamada, N." box="[877,1090,1095,1121]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="1" refId="ref4071" refString="Benetti, C. J., Valladares, L. F., Delgado, J. A. &amp; Hamada, N. (2021) Morphological remarks on Adelphydraena amazonica Perkins &amp; Ribera, 2020 and new records of two other Hydraenidae from Brazil (Coleoptera). Zootaxa, 4966 (1), 061 - 068. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4966.1.6" type="journal article" year="2021">
Benetti 
<emphasis box="[967,1023,1095,1121]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
